bug.short_desc: [abrt] xfce4-xkb-plugin: g_type_check_instance_is_a(): xfce4-xkb-plugin killed by SIGSEGV
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Description of problem: - crash seems to happen with Fedora 22 as well; not reporting it, since F22 will soon be end-of-life - using Xfce as desktop environment with LightDM as desktop manager - connect from Mac OS X 10.10.5 with X2Go 4.0.5.1 to Fedora 24 - (crash happens with Mac OS X 10.11 too; I guess it does not matter) - Applications -- Settings -- Keyboard -- Layouts: [] Use system defaults - Applications -- Settings -- Keyboard -- Layouts: add German and English keyboard layout - Applications -- Settings -- Keyboard -- Layouts: [x] Use system defaults - Applications -- Log out... -- Log out - reconnect with X2Go client - left click on xfce4-keyboard-plugin; then it crashes
Version-Release number of selected component: xfce4-xkb-plugin-0.7.1-4.fc24
